1
00:00:50,925 --> 00:00:54,050
[GAGGARA JINGLES]

2
00:00:58,465 --> 00:01:21,757
♪ ♪

3
00:01:26,690 --> 00:01:29,024
Why did Appayya (Father)
vanish right in this spot?

4
00:01:29,197 --> 00:01:30,613
This is our place of origin, dear.

5
00:01:31,030 --> 00:01:32,488
Our ancestors lived here.

6
00:01:33,072 --> 00:01:34,530
It's a legend.

7
00:01:34,530 --> 00:01:36,322
[OFFICER] Send a
share to the office, okay?

8
00:01:39,988 --> 00:01:41,072
Kamala...

9
00:01:41,113 --> 00:01:42,280
What's happening?

10
00:01:44,363 --> 00:01:45,822
Move aside!
[GUN FIRES IN THE AIR]

11
00:01:45,863 --> 00:01:46,863
- Scoundrel!
- Hey, Rampa!

12
00:01:46,905 --> 00:01:47,947
What are you staring at?

13
00:01:48,405 --> 00:01:49,697
My Grandpa's gun.

14
00:01:49,863 --> 00:01:51,155
It fires at its will.

15
00:01:51,738 --> 00:01:52,822
Continue the story.

16
00:01:52,822 --> 00:01:54,030
Damn her punch landed well.

17
00:01:54,072 --> 00:01:55,238
What do you mean by a legend?

18
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:58,655
Eons ago, Eshwara's
Ganas roamed this land.

19
00:01:58,947 --> 00:02:00,072
Who are Ganas?

20
00:02:00,976 --> 00:02:02,530
The Daivas we believe in.

21
00:02:05,113 --> 00:02:06,905
A force that has become one with nature.

22
00:02:07,322 --> 00:02:09,905
Whenever mankind strays
into Adharma (unrighteousness).

23
00:02:09,947 --> 00:02:11,988
From the divine realm,
Lord Eshwara sends

24
00:02:11,988 --> 00:02:14,072
his Ganas to protect
Dharma (righteousness).

25
00:02:15,198 --> 00:02:18,822
Among those who came, was
the one we follow - Panjurli.

26
00:02:23,652 --> 00:02:27,361
But to drink the blood of those on the
path of Adharma came another Daiva.

27
00:02:29,796 --> 00:02:31,254
The fierce force, Guliga.

28
00:02:31,254 --> 00:02:33,671
[PRIMORDIAL SCREAM]

29
00:02:36,177 --> 00:02:39,915
All of these Ganas came
to dwell in this sacred land.

30
00:02:40,957 --> 00:02:43,665
Thousands of years ago, it was known as

31
00:02:43,665 --> 00:02:49,040
KANTARA - A LEGEND
CHAPTER 1

32
00:02:49,832 --> 00:02:51,999
It was the era of the Kadambas
who ruled over Banavasi.

33
00:02:52,915 --> 00:02:56,332
The Palegaras of the west stationed by the
sea, served as the Kadambas’ vassal kings.

34
00:03:02,453 --> 00:03:03,953
With the strength of his sword

35
00:03:03,978 --> 00:03:06,603
a man shed a river of blood and
became the king of the vassals.

36
00:03:07,295 --> 00:03:09,881
A monster in human guise.

37
00:03:10,915 --> 00:03:12,331
Vijayendra of Bangra.

38
00:03:14,375 --> 00:03:18,375
Unaware of the outside world,
our elders lived a peaceful life.

39
00:03:19,433 --> 00:03:21,516
Among them was Baidi,
a little girl with dreams.

40
00:03:25,667 --> 00:03:26,792
Jabbanna, look here.

41
00:03:31,089 --> 00:03:32,339
Looks beautiful, right?

42
00:03:32,964 --> 00:03:34,589
Did we just find a sacred stone?

43
00:03:38,230 --> 00:03:42,839
Our people, who worshipped nature,
stood there seeing the Daiva in the stone.

44
00:03:45,938 --> 00:03:48,105
Blood ran through the shallow waters.

45
00:03:51,756 --> 00:03:54,131
One man stood
watching it all from afar.

46
00:03:54,673 --> 00:03:55,798
Maayakaara

47
00:04:00,923 --> 00:04:05,423
[BAIDI WAILING]

48
00:04:05,464 --> 00:04:06,589
JABBANNA!

49
00:04:06,631 --> 00:04:09,673
Our strong ancestors ended up
as slaves to Bangra's kingdom.

50
00:04:11,589 --> 00:04:12,631
[WHIP CRACKS]

51
00:04:12,631 --> 00:04:14,173
[LEVER CLANKS]

52
00:04:14,173 --> 00:04:17,464
[MAN SCREAMS IN AGONY]

53
00:04:18,923 --> 00:04:20,006
Gosh! Jabba!

54
00:04:42,756 --> 00:04:45,089
One day, when the King
was taking a bath in the ocean.

55
00:04:46,006 --> 00:04:48,589
Maayakaara was sitting
far away, dropping a hook.

56
00:04:56,173 --> 00:04:57,214
[SWORD CLANGS]

57
00:04:57,673 --> 00:05:00,298
Hey! His blood
shouldn't touch the water!

58
00:05:04,943 --> 00:05:08,235
Seeing the spices, the king's eyes lit up.

59
00:05:09,548 --> 00:05:13,964
Though it lacked the shine of silver or
gold, it was the foundation of their trade.

60
00:05:14,339 --> 00:05:15,506
Where did you find this?

61
00:05:16,131 --> 00:05:17,673
Lord Eshwara's garden of bloom

62
00:05:18,964 --> 00:05:20,006
Kantara.

63
00:05:21,214 --> 00:05:22,881
The king had everything.

64
00:05:23,589 --> 00:05:25,048
Except for Kantara.

65
00:05:36,631 --> 00:05:37,923
We're on the right path, right?

66
00:05:37,923 --> 00:05:40,089
[FOREST AMBIENT NOISES]

67
00:05:40,131 --> 00:05:42,464
- Where did the old man go?!
- He was right here!

68
00:05:42,464 --> 00:05:45,131
The king had fallen into the
Maayakaara's magical trap.

69
00:05:51,423 --> 00:05:52,548
[EERIE NOISE]

70
00:06:11,812 --> 00:06:13,756
[HORSE PANICS AND NEIGHS]

71
00:06:19,903 --> 00:06:22,070
He took in everything
the light revealed.

72
00:06:22,298 --> 00:06:23,839
Lord Eshwara's garden of bloom

73
00:06:23,881 --> 00:06:25,381
But it wasn't just light.

74
00:06:36,298 --> 00:06:39,423
[WILD OXEN CHARGE FURIOUSLY]

75
00:06:41,881 --> 00:06:43,339
[TREE BRANCH SNAPS]

76
00:06:43,839 --> 00:06:45,923
Appa (Father)! It's burning!

77
00:06:47,464 --> 00:06:49,923
[PRIMORDIAL SCREAM]

78
00:06:49,964 --> 00:06:51,089
Wait right here!

79
00:06:57,173 --> 00:06:58,381
[EERIE NOISE]

80
00:07:00,631 --> 00:07:01,673
[EERIE NOISE]

81
00:07:11,964 --> 00:07:13,048
[EERIE NOISE]

82
00:07:17,423 --> 00:07:18,673
[EERIE NOISE AT A DISTANCE]

83
00:07:26,382 --> 00:07:29,007
[VIJAYENDRA SCREAMS]

84
00:07:39,506 --> 00:07:40,798
Appa!

85
00:07:40,839 --> 00:07:43,381
[TREE CRACKLING IN FLAMES]

86
00:07:46,131 --> 00:07:47,631
What happened to the tree?!

87
00:07:48,256 --> 00:07:50,298
Well, there goes the king of Bangra!

88
00:07:50,339 --> 00:07:51,464
Huh?!
[GASP IN UNISON]

89
00:07:57,756 --> 00:07:58,964
[GOES INTO TRANCE]

90
00:08:07,381 --> 00:08:10,214
[PRIMORDIAL SCREAM]

91
00:08:10,256 --> 00:08:11,673
Swami Panjurli is here.

92
00:08:11,673 --> 00:08:16,548
[IN TULU] If anyone steps onto the land of
sacred stone with destruction in their heart

93
00:08:16,798 --> 00:08:19,589
Their blood shall be cleansed
only when it spills on this sacred soil!

94
00:08:19,756 --> 00:08:22,548
[PRIMORDIAL SCREAM]

95
00:08:22,548 --> 00:08:27,256
Let my voice, which has
crossed lands in the air

96
00:08:27,548 --> 00:08:29,798
Let it deliver this
message to all who hear it

97
00:08:30,006 --> 00:08:31,714
And let it leave their ears trembling!

98
00:08:32,006 --> 00:08:36,048
[PRIMORDIAL SCREAM]

99
00:08:40,589 --> 00:08:44,548
Rajashekhara, who ran into the forest in
a frenzy, headed straight toward Kadapa.

100
00:08:48,756 --> 00:08:51,381
While some found
peace through worship

101
00:08:52,131 --> 00:08:55,131
Others were out there, seeking
power through summoning.

102
00:08:56,131 --> 00:08:58,506
From the story Rajashekhara
told about the sacred stones,

103
00:08:58,548 --> 00:09:01,673
the Kadapa people set their
eyes on Kantara's powers.

104
00:09:02,048 --> 00:09:05,214
With the help of the Kadapa tribe,
Rajashekhara returned to his kingdom.

105
00:09:05,881 --> 00:09:08,381
Thus, darkness and
hideousness became one.

106
00:09:22,256 --> 00:09:26,589
Decades passed, yet the fear of
Kantara lived on in Rajashekhara’s heart.

107
00:09:27,298 --> 00:09:31,089
Whenever the land of Dharma grows parched,
the Ullaaya (Almighty) brings rain.

108
00:09:31,756 --> 00:09:34,714
Thus, divine forces are born
in this soil, again and again.

109
00:09:36,756 --> 00:09:38,173
[BABY COOING]

110
00:09:38,173 --> 00:09:40,673
Jabbanna, look here!
There's a baby in the well!

111
00:09:41,369 --> 00:09:44,035
Baidi chose to take in
the child nobody wanted.

112
00:09:47,249 --> 00:09:49,457
Found at the Daivas'
origin, he was named...

113
00:09:49,714 --> 00:09:50,798
Berme.

114
00:09:52,714 --> 00:09:55,339
Back in Bangra, Rajashekhara
fathered two children.

115
00:09:55,381 --> 00:10:00,381
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYS]

116
00:10:06,463 --> 00:10:09,588
But when he learned that the girl child
had no strength in her arms or legs...

117
00:10:16,173 --> 00:10:17,673
[BABY COOS]

118
00:10:28,714 --> 00:10:30,964
Why is this known as
Eshwara's garden of bloom?

119
00:10:32,464 --> 00:10:35,006
When our beloved Lord Shiva
came here to perform his penance

120
00:10:35,048 --> 00:10:38,381
Goddess Parvathi created this
garden so he could meditate in peace.

121
00:10:38,631 --> 00:10:40,298
Who is Berme talking to?

122
00:10:40,339 --> 00:10:41,548
Has he lost it?

123
00:10:41,673 --> 00:10:45,214
You picked an abandoned infant
and are asking me if it's sane?

124
00:10:45,256 --> 00:10:47,089
What can I do?
Come. Let's go.

125
00:10:47,131 --> 00:10:50,173
As he grew up, Berme was
in awe of the sacred stones.

126
00:10:50,714 --> 00:10:54,381
You should never step
into Kantara, my children.

127
00:10:54,423 --> 00:10:55,589
But why?

128
00:10:55,589 --> 00:10:58,798
There lives a Brahma-rakshasa.

129
00:10:58,839 --> 00:11:00,423
[BOY LAUGHS]

130
00:11:00,714 --> 00:11:02,673
What are you sniggering about?

131
00:11:03,048 --> 00:11:04,214
Don't laugh.

132
00:11:04,256 --> 00:11:05,756
There lives a Brahma-rakshasa!

133
00:11:07,189 --> 00:11:11,189
Years passed and our ancestors,
who used the forest’s resources to live

134
00:11:11,964 --> 00:11:16,131
left a share for the Daivas
and kept another for themselves.

135
00:11:16,589 --> 00:11:19,048
The third share was left
at the edge of the forest.

136
00:11:24,339 --> 00:11:27,881
They were made to believe that the
Brahma-Rakshasa would take that share.

137
00:11:28,714 --> 00:11:31,214
For Kantara and
Bangra's next generation,

138
00:11:31,256 --> 00:11:33,381
the fear of the Brahma-Rakshasa
became the boundary.

139
00:11:34,256 --> 00:11:35,923
[EERIE NOISE]

140
00:11:42,964 --> 00:11:46,548
As he aged, Rajashekhara
crowned his son King.

141
00:11:46,589 --> 00:11:56,214
[CELEBRATORY TRADITIONAL MUSIC]

142
00:12:04,256 --> 00:12:05,881
The King of the kings.

143
00:12:05,923 --> 00:12:07,506
The Regal Emperor.

144
00:12:07,756 --> 00:12:09,506
The Supreme Ruler of the People.

145
00:12:09,673 --> 00:12:11,589
The Lord of Bangra.

146
00:12:11,839 --> 00:12:14,673
The redeemer of Sri Rajashekhara's lineage.

147
00:12:14,714 --> 00:12:17,756
The new ruler of the Bangra throne.

148
00:12:17,798 --> 00:12:21,464
His Holiness King Kulashekhara.

149
00:12:21,756 --> 00:12:24,798
All hail! All hail! All hail!

150
00:12:24,798 --> 00:12:28,381
[CEREMONIAL HORN RESONATES]

151
00:12:28,381 --> 00:12:29,881
Kanakavathi, let's go.

152
00:12:32,631 --> 00:12:35,298
Kulashekhara, bow down to
the Rajaguru (The Royal Guru)!

153
00:12:35,839 --> 00:12:37,214
My my! The priest's here!

154
00:12:37,214 --> 00:12:38,464
Namaskara (Greetings)!

155
00:12:41,256 --> 00:12:42,548
May God bless you!

156
00:12:42,964 --> 00:12:44,381
Which God?

157
00:12:44,839 --> 00:12:47,798
All you need are my blessings.

158
00:12:49,339 --> 00:12:50,548
Wishing you well. Carry on.

159
00:12:56,423 --> 00:12:58,173
A gift from the
Kadambas to the King.

160
00:13:02,589 --> 00:13:04,339
My King! Whoa!

161
00:13:05,923 --> 00:13:07,214
Can I take a look?

162
00:13:07,214 --> 00:13:09,173
- It's shining, right?
- Look how awesome it is!

163
00:13:10,756 --> 00:13:11,964
- My King!
- So heavy!

164
00:13:15,339 --> 00:13:17,339
When the kingdom was
prospering under your rule

165
00:13:17,381 --> 00:13:19,589
Was it truly necessary
to crown your son?

166
00:13:20,471 --> 00:13:22,846
My father never got to
see me ascend the throne.

167
00:13:23,506 --> 00:13:25,964
What I couldn't do for my father

168
00:13:26,214 --> 00:13:28,423
I believe my son will achieve.

169
00:13:28,464 --> 00:13:29,631
Will he really be able to?

170
00:13:31,256 --> 00:13:32,839
I'm with him, aren't I?

171
00:13:34,256 --> 00:13:38,381
As King, you made me
your minister, Kulashekhara.

172
00:13:38,881 --> 00:13:41,048
We must find a
way to celebrate this.

173
00:13:41,339 --> 00:13:42,631
Celebrate how?

174
00:13:42,923 --> 00:13:44,964
Wars ended during my father's reign.

175
00:13:45,298 --> 00:13:47,756
[GUNANANDA] You still
need to rule, don't you?

176
00:13:47,798 --> 00:13:49,339
Well, you're right.

177
00:13:50,173 --> 00:13:51,881
Shall we kick things
off with a hunt?

178
00:13:51,964 --> 00:13:52,964
That's like it.

179
00:13:53,131 --> 00:13:54,506
Where do we go?

180
00:13:54,548 --> 00:13:55,714
Kantara.

181
00:13:55,923 --> 00:13:57,298
What a scary forest!

182
00:13:57,339 --> 00:13:59,714
Is there really a
Brahma-rakshasa in this forest?

183
00:14:00,173 --> 00:14:02,923
Didn’t your father claim
he saw it with his own eyes?

184
00:14:03,048 --> 00:14:05,381
Ah! Even if it's here,
what does it matter?

185
00:14:05,631 --> 00:14:07,756
The men up ahead will
run into it before we do.

186
00:14:07,798 --> 00:14:09,256
[BHOGENDRA CACKLES]

187
00:14:09,589 --> 00:14:11,381
No matter who gets
caught, I hope I don't.

188
00:14:11,923 --> 00:14:13,589
- AY BHOGENDRA!
- Yeah?

189
00:14:13,589 --> 00:14:15,339
Ride the chariot slowly!

190
00:14:15,381 --> 00:14:17,214
You're making me throw
up everything I drank!

191
00:14:17,214 --> 00:14:19,006
I can't go any slower than this.

192
00:14:19,298 --> 00:14:21,548
If it's that much trouble,
walk with the soldiers.

193
00:14:21,548 --> 00:14:22,548
What?!

194
00:14:22,589 --> 00:14:24,589
Can't tell who's king
or minister anymore.

195
00:14:28,744 --> 00:14:31,453
- Give me an arrow.
- Take this.

196
00:14:35,271 --> 00:14:36,729
- Give me the bow.
- Oh!

197
00:14:36,938 --> 00:14:38,521
I forgot the bow.

198
00:14:38,896 --> 00:14:40,604
Goddammit! This chimp brain!

199
00:14:40,604 --> 00:14:42,771
Shows up for a hunt
with arrows and no bow.

200
00:14:42,813 --> 00:14:44,396
What do I shoot this
with now, dumbo?

201
00:14:44,771 --> 00:14:45,938
Sire! Excuse me?

202
00:14:46,188 --> 00:14:47,813
Please tell the King to keep it low.

203
00:14:47,854 --> 00:14:49,271
Give me the bow, moron!

204
00:14:51,896 --> 00:14:53,479
Annu, somebody's
definitely there.

205
00:14:58,604 --> 00:14:59,729
What happened?

206
00:15:01,063 --> 00:15:02,479
Something flew by me.

207
00:15:02,521 --> 00:15:04,271
Man has zero survival instincts!

208
00:15:04,271 --> 00:15:05,979
Hey! Keep an eye out!

209
00:15:06,604 --> 00:15:08,021
- Langur! Langur!
- Where?!

210
00:15:09,729 --> 00:15:11,104
[LANGUR SCREAMS IN PAIN]

211
00:15:13,313 --> 00:15:15,896
Bravo Madhukara!
That was a damn good shot!

212
00:15:15,896 --> 00:15:17,604
- Of course. I showed him.
- Really?

213
00:15:17,604 --> 00:15:19,563
- Bring the prey!
- Guards in the front, go on!

214
00:15:21,979 --> 00:15:23,813
If you hear anything
inside, give us a 'Coo'.

215
00:15:23,896 --> 00:15:26,521
- Are you going further inside?
- I'm not an idiot! I'll just run!

216
00:15:27,021 --> 00:15:28,646
- Sire, there's nothing here.
- Huh?

217
00:15:29,854 --> 00:15:31,354
Hey! He did shoot the arrow, right?

218
00:15:31,354 --> 00:15:32,604
Yeah. He did.

219
00:15:32,646 --> 00:15:34,688
King, isn't it better we
don't continue further?

220
00:15:34,979 --> 00:15:37,063
- Shall we go?
- Yeah. Let's go.

221
00:15:37,063 --> 00:15:38,146
Hey, go forward!

222
00:15:38,188 --> 00:15:39,354
Dammit!

223
00:15:40,271 --> 00:15:42,896
This is a good horse.
Listens to every single order.

224
00:15:42,979 --> 00:15:45,146
He got coronated,
but we'll get cremated!

225
00:15:45,188 --> 00:15:46,313
Hey! A stag!

226
00:15:47,604 --> 00:15:49,063
[ARROW RELEASES AND STRIKES]

227
00:15:49,646 --> 00:15:51,229
It's running!

228
00:15:53,521 --> 00:15:54,646
Stop the chariot!

229
00:15:54,646 --> 00:15:57,146
Bravo! What a shot, King!

230
00:15:57,188 --> 00:15:58,271
A great shot!

231
00:15:58,313 --> 00:15:59,313
I know.

232
00:15:59,604 --> 00:16:01,188
Hey! Get it!

233
00:16:02,146 --> 00:16:03,938
Annu, let's be done
with this and hurry home!

234
00:16:03,979 --> 00:16:06,313
Kulashekhara, we'll carry
it in our chariot, okay?

235
00:16:06,313 --> 00:16:08,688
People shouldn't think the
King returned empty handed.

236
00:16:09,729 --> 00:16:11,021
The Brahma-rakshasa!

237
00:16:11,313 --> 00:16:13,771
[OMINOUS ATMOSPHERE]

238
00:16:13,813 --> 00:16:16,646
Great Lord, isn't it better
we leave now.. What?!

239
00:16:16,646 --> 00:16:17,771
[HORSE GALLOPS]

240
00:16:20,604 --> 00:16:21,604
He took my bow.

241
00:16:21,646 --> 00:16:22,979
SOLDIERS!
[SOLDIERS GASP IN FEAR]

242
00:16:22,979 --> 00:16:24,854
Fear not! Keep watch
in all four directions!

243
00:16:24,854 --> 00:16:26,729
[ARROW STRIKES; ANNU COLLAPSES]

244
00:16:27,354 --> 00:16:28,396
RUN!

245
00:16:28,604 --> 00:16:29,938
[BODY THUDS AGAINST THE TREE]

246
00:16:40,229 --> 00:16:41,354
Who was that?

247
00:16:42,438 --> 00:16:44,229
Nagendra, stop acting like an idiot!

248
00:16:45,563 --> 00:16:47,688
He was the last of the brave ones.
He's gone too.

249
00:16:50,104 --> 00:16:51,813
If we all die, who’ll
tell our families?!

250
00:16:51,813 --> 00:16:53,021
My God!

251
00:16:54,188 --> 00:16:57,188
[SOLDIER SCREAMS IN HORROR]

252
00:17:01,438 --> 00:17:02,479
[ARROW PIERCES]

253
00:17:07,021 --> 00:17:08,813
Brahma-rakshasa's boulder!

254
00:17:11,396 --> 00:17:12,438
Thus, we're done.

255
00:17:15,021 --> 00:17:17,188
Stop staring and check it out!

256
00:17:18,021 --> 00:17:19,354
Didn't you hear me? Go!

257
00:17:22,313 --> 00:17:23,396
Good Lord!

258
00:17:36,688 --> 00:17:40,771
[SOLDIERS CLASH WITH THE TRIBALS]

259
00:18:18,063 --> 00:18:19,771
[TRIBAL SCREAMS FURIOUSLY]

260
00:18:19,771 --> 00:18:20,896
GOD!

261
00:18:21,396 --> 00:18:22,438
I made it out alive!

262
00:18:22,479 --> 00:18:23,771
All thanks to the
guy in the sky!

263
00:18:25,563 --> 00:18:29,979
[HEROIC MUSIC]

264
00:18:32,021 --> 00:18:33,313
Wohoo! Berme!

265
00:18:33,646 --> 00:18:35,896
Looks like I got here
a little late, didn't I?

266
00:18:35,938 --> 00:18:36,938
[ROPE SNAPS]

267
00:18:36,938 --> 00:18:42,438
♪ ♪

268
00:18:45,313 --> 00:18:46,604
♪ The Ullaaya of the forest ♪

269
00:18:46,604 --> 00:18:49,271
♪ The garden where Lord
Eshwara planted the flowers ♪

270
00:18:50,521 --> 00:18:51,854
♪ The land shaped by Berme ♪

271
00:18:51,896 --> 00:18:55,563
♪ The soil that holds the Daivas ♪

272
00:18:55,604 --> 00:18:57,104
♪ This is the land of Kantara ♪

273
00:18:57,438 --> 00:19:02,146
[TRIBALS CONTINUE TO SING]

274
00:19:08,313 --> 00:19:09,604
Oh. Jabbanna's here.

275
00:19:09,896 --> 00:19:11,188
You guys continue.

276
00:19:11,688 --> 00:19:13,771
What are you children up to?

277
00:19:14,479 --> 00:19:15,813
- Pampi...
- Oh?

278
00:19:16,146 --> 00:19:17,438
How was my hunt?

279
00:19:17,521 --> 00:19:18,688
Killed it, didn’t I?

280
00:19:18,729 --> 00:19:20,146
You killed our damn spirit.

281
00:19:20,271 --> 00:19:22,479
The next time you trail us,
we'll shower you with stones.

282
00:19:22,521 --> 00:19:24,229
What nonsense are you blabbering?

283
00:19:24,951 --> 00:19:26,729
You got scared and
ran like hell, right?

284
00:19:26,729 --> 00:19:28,438
It wasn’t even a
tiger, just a porcupine.

285
00:19:28,479 --> 00:19:29,979
It froze because I screamed!

286
00:19:30,021 --> 00:19:32,271
Oy Grandpa! It spiked up and froze.

287
00:19:32,313 --> 00:19:34,063
Hasn’t moved since. Take it.

288
00:19:34,271 --> 00:19:35,854
Quit questioning my capability.

289
00:19:35,854 --> 00:19:37,479
Give it to me! Argh!

290
00:19:37,479 --> 00:19:38,521
Yeah, right!

291
00:19:38,813 --> 00:19:40,063
Stop your nonsense.

292
00:19:40,104 --> 00:19:43,063
You had no reason to test
your capability on me at this age.

293
00:19:43,104 --> 00:19:45,688
[WOMEN LAUGH IN UNISON]

294
00:19:45,688 --> 00:19:47,396
Nochchi! Take this!

295
00:19:48,229 --> 00:19:49,313
There you go.

296
00:19:49,313 --> 00:19:50,396
You led a good hunt today.

297
00:19:50,438 --> 00:19:56,313
[MEN HOLLERING]

298
00:19:56,938 --> 00:19:58,563
Ay Kura! What are
you always scratching?!

299
00:19:58,563 --> 00:20:00,396
Abba, we had a great hunt today.

300
00:20:00,438 --> 00:20:05,104
[OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

301
00:20:05,146 --> 00:20:06,188
Huh?

302
00:20:06,646 --> 00:20:10,979
[WARNING CALLS]

303
00:20:15,438 --> 00:20:16,646
Hey! This one's alive!

304
00:20:17,146 --> 00:20:21,021
[HUNTERS HOWL]

305
00:20:21,021 --> 00:20:22,729
I died a long time ago.

306
00:20:24,479 --> 00:20:25,896
- HEY!
- JABBANNA STOP!

307
00:20:25,896 --> 00:20:27,771
He blacked out after seeing us.

308
00:20:30,938 --> 00:20:32,438
Which scumbag brought him here?

309
00:20:32,438 --> 00:20:33,604
They came by themselves.

310
00:20:33,771 --> 00:20:35,479
- How many?
- Many.

311
00:20:35,771 --> 00:20:37,354
We killed everyone
we laid our hands on.

312
00:20:37,396 --> 00:20:38,729
The ones on the horses escaped.

313
00:20:40,146 --> 00:20:41,229
It's the King.

314
00:20:46,396 --> 00:20:48,188
The people of Bangra
have crossed the border.

315
00:20:48,729 --> 00:20:50,896
They’ll try to drag our
people back into slavery.

316
00:20:51,229 --> 00:20:53,396
Sleep with a weapon
under your head.

317
00:20:54,688 --> 00:20:55,854
What cowards, man!

318
00:20:56,146 --> 00:20:57,896
They ran without
even looking at us.

319
00:20:58,313 --> 00:20:59,438
And they're scared of them.

320
00:21:00,063 --> 00:21:02,646
My thought is, the people of
Bangra have already made the way.

321
00:21:02,854 --> 00:21:05,479
Before they return, we
better cross it ourselves.

322
00:21:05,521 --> 00:21:07,313
Should we tell
Jabba just to be safe?

323
00:21:07,354 --> 00:21:08,438
Yeah, right!

324
00:21:08,646 --> 00:21:11,188
He left our people behind
because they chopped his toes.

325
00:21:11,188 --> 00:21:12,729
How will he even keep us safe?

326
00:21:13,271 --> 00:21:14,771
I’m saying this because I’ve seen it.

327
00:21:14,813 --> 00:21:16,188
Nah! You ran first!

328
00:21:16,229 --> 00:21:17,813
I know what they’re capable of.

329
00:21:18,563 --> 00:21:20,604
From now on, the border
watchers must stay alert.

330
00:21:21,354 --> 00:21:22,604
- Berme!
- Yeah?

331
00:21:22,813 --> 00:21:24,563
Dispose the bodies outside the border.

332
00:21:24,721 --> 00:21:26,846
Let no more people
come looking for them.

333
00:21:26,871 --> 00:21:27,954
Yeah. Sure.

334
00:21:29,194 --> 00:21:31,111
Phew! Jabba said the same thing.

335
00:21:31,136 --> 00:21:32,220
Cross the border!

336
00:21:32,245 --> 00:21:34,162
What about the Brahma-Rakshasa?

337
00:21:34,187 --> 00:21:36,312
- It's all a cooked up story!
- Really?

338
00:21:37,813 --> 00:21:40,354
Berme, shouldn't we at least
know which direction to take?

339
00:21:40,688 --> 00:21:42,229
We've got a guiding
spirit, don't we?

340
00:21:42,271 --> 00:21:43,438
Dodda, hand me the axe.

341
00:21:43,563 --> 00:21:45,688
If he’s been out this
long, I doubt he’ll wake up.

342
00:21:46,354 --> 00:21:47,938
- Better to kill him, right?
- Yes!

343
00:21:48,771 --> 00:21:50,104
- HEY!
- WAIT!

344
00:21:50,146 --> 00:21:51,729
I'm back. Tell me.

345
00:21:52,468 --> 00:21:55,010
Did we have to do this at
the edge of the waterfalls?

346
00:21:55,121 --> 00:21:56,288
My legs are trembling!

347
00:21:56,385 --> 00:21:58,760
What stone is this?
It's sharp as hell!

348
00:21:59,271 --> 00:22:01,104
This isn't stone.
It's iron.

349
00:22:01,146 --> 00:22:02,646
Our Sankappa makes them.

350
00:22:02,688 --> 00:22:04,938
Don't eat iron.
Your tongue will rust.

351
00:22:05,938 --> 00:22:07,146
- Hello! Sire?
- Yeah?

352
00:22:07,188 --> 00:22:08,563
How far is your place from here?

353
00:22:08,938 --> 00:22:12,021
It's a day's journey by walk.

354
00:22:12,146 --> 00:22:14,063
- You'll take us, right?
- Sure. Wait!

355
00:22:14,354 --> 00:22:15,563
Why do you guys want to come?

356
00:22:15,563 --> 00:22:17,771
Shouldn’t we see
how far you’ve come?

357
00:22:17,771 --> 00:22:18,813
And?

358
00:22:18,854 --> 00:22:20,104
We'll return after, won't we?

359
00:22:20,604 --> 00:22:22,729
If they find out that
I got you guys there

360
00:22:22,771 --> 00:22:24,688
My life there too will
turn into a living hell.

361
00:22:24,729 --> 00:22:26,646
Why do you think
you're taking us?

362
00:22:26,646 --> 00:22:28,188
We're coming there drop you.

363
00:22:29,021 --> 00:22:30,438
Sure that's what you think.

364
00:22:30,479 --> 00:22:31,938
But they should get it, right?

365
00:22:32,146 --> 00:22:33,146
God!

366
00:22:33,146 --> 00:22:35,021
Okay then. Let's
pray to him and leave.

367
00:22:35,229 --> 00:22:36,354
- What?!
- Yeah.

368
00:22:36,938 --> 00:22:39,188
We're crossing the forest
boundary for the first time.

369
00:22:39,188 --> 00:22:40,438
The rest is on you.

370
00:22:40,563 --> 00:22:41,729
Bless us, Swami Panjurli.

371
00:22:41,729 --> 00:22:42,813
Swami Panjurli.
[IN UNISON]

372
00:22:42,813 --> 00:22:44,979
- What's happening?
- That is the Daiva we believe in.

373
00:22:45,188 --> 00:22:46,729
I swear I don’t see anything.

374
00:22:46,729 --> 00:22:48,396
You need true
devotion to see it.

375
00:22:48,438 --> 00:22:50,271
Doesn’t matter. Just
pray with your heart.

376
00:22:56,646 --> 00:22:57,979
I can now see it too.

377
00:23:00,146 --> 00:23:01,229
I forgot to tell you.

378
00:23:01,229 --> 00:23:03,354
Nobody but soldiers are
allowed to cross the border!

379
00:23:03,521 --> 00:23:05,563
Now they will, won't they?
Good plan.

380
00:23:05,563 --> 00:23:07,188
Phew! Thank God I'm alive!

381
00:23:07,479 --> 00:23:09,146
I don't even wear anything inside.

382
00:23:09,688 --> 00:23:11,646
Listen, what is a Brahma-rakshasa?

383
00:23:11,688 --> 00:23:12,729
It's nothing.

384
00:23:12,771 --> 00:23:14,396
- Once...
- Quiet. Let me tell him.

385
00:23:14,396 --> 00:23:16,563
Once upon a time,
there was an evil king.

386
00:23:16,563 --> 00:23:17,729
Wait, we have one too.

387
00:23:17,771 --> 00:23:19,313
YEAH. HIM.
[IN UNISON]

388
00:23:20,188 --> 00:23:21,896
He couldn't find anyone to work.

389
00:23:22,021 --> 00:23:23,354
So he performed a great penance.

390
00:23:23,396 --> 00:23:25,313
Why a penance?
He could have just paid more!

391
00:23:25,313 --> 00:23:27,021
- Just listen. Will you?
- Don't interrupt.

392
00:23:27,063 --> 00:23:29,354
Sages and saints offered
him a man as a helper and said -

393
00:23:29,354 --> 00:23:31,313
"Give him so much work
that he has no free time."

394
00:23:31,313 --> 00:23:32,396
Why's that?

395
00:23:32,396 --> 00:23:34,354
If you let him free,
he'll eat humans.

396
00:23:34,396 --> 00:23:35,729
- My God!
- Yeah!

397
00:23:35,729 --> 00:23:37,688
- There's more.
- Let me continue.

398
00:23:37,688 --> 00:23:40,104
You can stop here.
I’ve lost my zeal.

399
00:23:40,104 --> 00:23:41,604
Already? Let me fill you up.

400
00:23:41,646 --> 00:23:43,646
- There's more for you to know.
- This is enough.

401
00:23:43,688 --> 00:23:46,854
- My heartbeat's really high.
- We'll stop that. Don't worry.

402
00:23:46,896 --> 00:23:48,354
He did exactly as told.

403
00:23:48,354 --> 00:23:50,688
When jobless, he
would gobble humans.

404
00:23:50,688 --> 00:23:52,688
One time, he was about to eat the King.

405
00:23:52,688 --> 00:23:54,813
The queen immediately
pulled out a curly hair strand,

406
00:23:54,813 --> 00:23:56,146
and asked him to straighten it.

407
00:23:56,188 --> 00:23:57,813
- Did he straighten it?
- No way!

408
00:23:58,021 --> 00:24:00,063
He's still busy straightening
it out in the forest.

409
00:24:00,063 --> 00:24:01,771
Who is this idiot?!

410
00:24:01,813 --> 00:24:03,021
The Brahma-rakshasa!

411
00:24:03,021 --> 00:24:05,563
- What?! Him?!
- Yep!

412
00:24:05,604 --> 00:24:06,646
Good Lord!

413
00:24:06,646 --> 00:24:09,063
What if he straightens it
and appears in front of me?

414
00:24:09,104 --> 00:24:10,271
He'll straighten me out!

415
00:24:13,813 --> 00:24:15,729
All I want now is to meet Jayanthi.

416
00:24:16,063 --> 00:24:18,021
- Who's that?
- A chunk of the crescent moon.

417
00:24:18,188 --> 00:24:19,188
Ah.

418
00:24:20,563 --> 00:24:21,646
What's that?

419
00:24:22,979 --> 00:24:24,063
Bangra's walls.

420
00:24:29,229 --> 00:24:30,563
Did Sankappa build this too?

421
00:24:30,563 --> 00:24:33,188
Yes. This was the first
move of King Rajashekhara.

422
00:24:33,229 --> 00:24:34,396
Open the gates!

423
00:24:37,688 --> 00:24:40,063
Berme, our clothes would've busted us here.

424
00:24:40,063 --> 00:24:41,979
Shut up and walk straight!

425
00:24:41,979 --> 00:24:43,563
Oy Chenna! The king
returned yesterday.

426
00:24:43,604 --> 00:24:44,688
What took you so long?

427
00:24:44,729 --> 00:24:46,729
Well, the forest had
plenty to explore.

428
00:24:46,771 --> 00:24:48,729
- Then where's the prey?
- Right here!

429
00:24:49,521 --> 00:24:50,563
Please shut your traps!

430
00:24:50,604 --> 00:24:53,521
- Attending the King's first assembly?
- Maybe if I'm free.

431
00:24:57,479 --> 00:24:58,813
What's taking the King so long?

432
00:24:59,104 --> 00:25:03,104
The king rises early, meditates, prays,
then lights the lamp before coming here.

433
00:25:03,313 --> 00:25:04,396
So, naturally he's late.

434
00:25:05,146 --> 00:25:07,896
This is what I love
about you, King.

435
00:25:08,104 --> 00:25:10,063
Even after taking the throne

436
00:25:10,313 --> 00:25:12,729
You haven’t changed a bit.

437
00:25:13,104 --> 00:25:15,521
You're still the same old Kulashekhara.

438
00:25:15,604 --> 00:25:17,063
Bhogendra, It's noon already!

439
00:25:17,104 --> 00:25:18,646
The assembly's waiting! Hurry up!

440
00:25:19,146 --> 00:25:20,771
- We will.
- Noon already, huh?

441
00:25:22,229 --> 00:25:23,396
Kulashekhara!

442
00:25:24,021 --> 00:25:26,688
This is your first
assembly as a king!

443
00:25:29,354 --> 00:25:31,354
They shouldn't find out we're drunk.

444
00:25:32,979 --> 00:25:34,146
Nuh-uh!

445
00:25:34,438 --> 00:25:36,063
No way they'll know!

446
00:25:36,063 --> 00:25:39,938
[METALLIC OBJECT ROLLS DOWN]

447
00:25:41,938 --> 00:25:43,313
Slow down! God!

448
00:25:48,188 --> 00:25:49,771
Don't let them know
that you're drunk.

449
00:26:06,104 --> 00:26:08,563
Hope they don't
know we're drunk.

450
00:26:08,688 --> 00:26:09,771
No way!

451
00:26:13,979 --> 00:26:15,729
Let the assembly begin.

452
00:26:16,688 --> 00:26:18,604
Whoa man! What a spectacle!

453
00:26:18,813 --> 00:26:19,896
Awesome, right?

454
00:26:21,021 --> 00:26:22,188
- Hey!
- What?

455
00:26:22,729 --> 00:26:24,063
Princess Kanakavathi is here.

456
00:26:24,104 --> 00:26:25,313
She shouldn't spot us.

457
00:26:25,354 --> 00:26:27,188
Yeah? Let's see if we can spot her.

458
00:26:27,188 --> 00:26:29,354
- Let's check them out!
- Stop! I've somehow survived.

459
00:26:29,396 --> 00:26:30,896
Don’t drain what little of me is left.

460
00:26:31,063 --> 00:26:32,271
Guys! Listen up!

461
00:26:32,313 --> 00:26:33,646
I mean it! Listen to me!

462
00:26:33,938 --> 00:26:35,271
Gosh! Look at the crowd!

463
00:26:35,271 --> 00:26:36,813
- Listen!
- What's that tall thing?

464
00:26:36,813 --> 00:26:38,396
It's tall but doesn't
rise when needed.

465
00:26:38,479 --> 00:26:39,563
Sir, please.

466
00:26:39,563 --> 00:26:40,896
Where is he busy looking?!

467
00:26:40,938 --> 00:26:42,063
[TASKMASTER ORDERS]

468
00:26:45,063 --> 00:26:46,396
HEY! LIFT IT!

469
00:26:49,938 --> 00:26:52,063
If your hands touch the
water, I’ll slaughter you.

470
00:26:52,104 --> 00:26:53,521
[SLAVES SCREAM IN PAIN]

471
00:26:55,479 --> 00:26:56,521
Genda!

472
00:26:56,771 --> 00:26:57,979
What is it? Huh?

473
00:26:59,438 --> 00:27:00,979
- Food!
- I'm dying out of hunger!

474
00:27:01,021 --> 00:27:02,229
Wait right here! Don’t move!

475
00:27:02,271 --> 00:27:04,021
God, I don’t know
who to control anymore.

476
00:27:04,063 --> 00:27:05,896
- God! I can breathe easy now.
- One for me.

477
00:27:05,896 --> 00:27:08,396
Looks like I should've gotten
them to eat before coming.

478
00:27:08,438 --> 00:27:10,688
- Why are you acting like savages?
- Oh. Hey Chenna!

479
00:27:10,729 --> 00:27:12,604
What?! Erm...

480
00:27:12,813 --> 00:27:15,688
- Veera Mahabalanna.
- Long time. No see.

481
00:27:15,729 --> 00:27:17,563
The king's assigned
me to secret service.

482
00:27:17,604 --> 00:27:18,646
So, I can't be seen.

483
00:27:18,688 --> 00:27:20,021
- Really?
- Super secret.

484
00:27:20,313 --> 00:27:22,146
Eat. Don’t let your hands go dry.

485
00:27:23,166 --> 00:27:24,625
Hurry and eat already!

486
00:27:40,813 --> 00:27:41,896
Priest?

487
00:27:45,188 --> 00:27:47,479
Please prepare a report
of everything done so far.

488
00:27:47,479 --> 00:27:48,854
Let me know what else you need.

489
00:27:48,896 --> 00:27:50,979
I will speak to the King
and arrange the permit.

490
00:27:53,854 --> 00:27:55,396
I see a sacred stone.

491
00:27:55,771 --> 00:27:56,854
Should we still sculpt it?

492
00:27:56,979 --> 00:27:59,229
The Kadambas have commissioned
such a magnificent temple.

493
00:27:59,604 --> 00:28:01,729
Shouldn't the God inside
look as good as the rest?

494
00:28:01,771 --> 00:28:03,563
- You may begin.
- Okay. As you wish.

495
00:28:08,627 --> 00:28:10,210
God! Protect us!

496
00:28:18,021 --> 00:28:20,396
Looks like we’re off
to an inauspicious start.

497
00:28:42,646 --> 00:28:43,979
[SCREAMS IN FEAR]

498
00:28:44,813 --> 00:28:46,396
Hiding here? Stay in!

499
00:28:46,438 --> 00:28:48,063
This is definitely a queen bee.

500
00:29:48,563 --> 00:29:49,771
Hey! Come here!

501
00:29:51,854 --> 00:29:53,438
- What is it?
- Are you a solider?

502
00:29:53,438 --> 00:29:55,063
So only a soldier
can rescue you now?

503
00:29:55,854 --> 00:29:58,563
Not leaving until they feed
you at my funeral, huh?

504
00:29:58,563 --> 00:30:00,354
Hey! Who cares who she is?!

505
00:30:00,938 --> 00:30:02,521
- Princess!
- I'm fine.

506
00:30:03,771 --> 00:30:06,646
[TRIBALS ULULATE]

507
00:30:07,063 --> 00:30:09,521
WOW! WHAT IS ALL THIS?

508
00:30:15,271 --> 00:30:17,313
Cheenkara! Wipe your mouth!
You're drooling!

509
00:30:19,063 --> 00:30:20,896
From here, we both go our own ways.

510
00:30:20,938 --> 00:30:22,896
Don't tell anybody
that I brought you here.

511
00:30:22,938 --> 00:30:24,854
Nah! We won't. Unless they ask.

512
00:30:24,896 --> 00:30:25,896
What?!

513
00:30:26,563 --> 00:30:28,771
Looks like I’m tomorrow's
fresh catch at the butcher’s.

514
00:30:32,396 --> 00:30:33,438
Tch tch!

515
00:30:35,354 --> 00:30:36,854
Hey! Chenna!

516
00:30:42,729 --> 00:30:44,521
All that adventure
will finally pay off!

517
00:30:45,604 --> 00:30:46,604
Hey!

518
00:30:46,646 --> 00:30:48,461
Look here! We've found Sankappa's place.

519
00:30:48,486 --> 00:30:50,528
Look at his inventions! What a genius!

520
00:30:52,813 --> 00:30:54,313
- What did you want?
- Well...

521
00:30:54,354 --> 00:30:55,563
Give me some of that.

522
00:30:55,938 --> 00:30:57,938
Some of this. For hunting.

523
00:30:57,938 --> 00:30:59,521
- A couple of these.
- What for?

524
00:30:59,521 --> 00:31:00,896
To bring back our prey.

525
00:31:01,229 --> 00:31:03,979
- The King's authorisation letter?
- You’ll give this only with that?

526
00:31:04,313 --> 00:31:05,896
Did you join the army yesterday?

527
00:31:05,938 --> 00:31:07,729
- Nah! This morning.
- Huh?

528
00:31:07,729 --> 00:31:08,729
Hey!

529
00:31:10,521 --> 00:31:11,938
Your armour's all dirty?

530
00:31:11,938 --> 00:31:13,563
About that...

531
00:31:13,604 --> 00:31:16,104
Gotcha! You came here right
after the training, didn't you?

532
00:31:16,104 --> 00:31:17,479
YES!

533
00:31:18,104 --> 00:31:20,479
If Sankappa was here, he
would've handed it over right away.

534
00:31:20,688 --> 00:31:22,313
I managed to catch
you red-handed.

535
00:31:22,354 --> 00:31:23,979
- Where is Sankappa?
- In the prison.

536
00:31:23,979 --> 00:31:25,021
Whose son?

537
00:31:27,188 --> 00:31:28,188
Jayanthi!

538
00:31:30,188 --> 00:31:31,563
Where were you all these days?

539
00:31:31,604 --> 00:31:33,021
Ugh. Never mind about that.

540
00:31:33,229 --> 00:31:35,229
Your wife has found
out all about us.

541
00:31:35,229 --> 00:31:37,313
- Which mongrel outed us?
- Veera Mahabalanna.

542
00:31:37,313 --> 00:31:39,729
Ugh! All these wars
and he never dies.

543
00:31:40,438 --> 00:31:41,563
To hell with him!

544
00:31:41,771 --> 00:31:42,938
Enough hide and seek.

545
00:31:43,271 --> 00:31:44,896
Come. Let’s speak, heart to heart.

546
00:31:46,104 --> 00:31:47,313
Look over there and hammer!

547
00:31:48,188 --> 00:31:50,604
I need to have a heartfelt
conversation here.

548
00:31:51,396 --> 00:31:52,438
Okay.

549
00:31:59,604 --> 00:32:01,438
- Aren't these things ours?
- Yeah man!

550
00:32:01,479 --> 00:32:02,813
Fragrant! The cinnamon is great!

551
00:32:02,813 --> 00:32:04,063
How did these things get here?

552
00:32:05,229 --> 00:32:06,396
How much for this?

553
00:32:06,396 --> 00:32:07,771
- Let's go!
- Take that off!

554
00:32:08,021 --> 00:32:11,021
Even if you slog all your life you
won't be able to buy a handful of these.

555
00:32:11,063 --> 00:32:13,063
- You think you can steal?!
- It's from our forest!

556
00:32:13,104 --> 00:32:14,979
Men like you should be hung to death!

557
00:32:15,021 --> 00:32:17,354
Soldiers! Let that be!
Grab him!

558
00:32:17,396 --> 00:32:19,729
You keep him. This is ours!
We'll keep this.

559
00:32:19,771 --> 00:32:21,688
Ay! Who the hell are you guys?

560
00:32:21,854 --> 00:32:23,104
You don't look like soldiers.

561
00:32:23,146 --> 00:32:26,354
Even with all this, if we don’t
look like soldiers, what’s the point?

562
00:32:26,354 --> 00:32:28,229
- Don't take it off!
- All of them are thieves!

563
00:32:28,271 --> 00:32:29,521
Soldiers! Come here!

564
00:32:29,604 --> 00:32:31,313
Grab them! Hurry up!

565
00:32:31,396 --> 00:32:33,521
- Frisk their clothes!
- Quit talking! Move!

566
00:32:33,563 --> 00:32:34,896
- Guys! Listen!
- Keep moving!

567
00:32:34,938 --> 00:32:37,313
- Don't you recognise us?!
- MOVE!

568
00:32:38,271 --> 00:32:41,938
[TRIBALS ULULATE]

569
00:32:42,979 --> 00:32:44,646
- Not all over again!
- Who is it?

570
00:32:44,729 --> 00:32:46,188
Those demons! Move!

571
00:32:46,188 --> 00:32:48,146
Where do I hide?!
Only God can guide me now!

572
00:32:53,146 --> 00:32:54,188
Want me to go there?

573
00:32:54,771 --> 00:32:56,438
These guys are all
over the king street!

574
00:32:56,438 --> 00:32:57,521
Nab them! Go!

575
00:33:01,604 --> 00:33:02,896
[BERME ULULATES]

576
00:33:12,771 --> 00:33:15,021
Not the ride I wanted. Morons!

577
00:33:15,063 --> 00:33:16,896
It won't be
comfortable up there.

578
00:33:16,938 --> 00:33:18,104
We had enough down there.

579
00:33:18,146 --> 00:33:19,813
Who asked you?
Get back to business!

580
00:33:19,813 --> 00:33:20,938
My fate!

581
00:33:40,563 --> 00:33:42,979
- Berme, looks like it's time to leave.
- Shut it!

582
00:33:44,438 --> 00:33:47,563
[SPEARS CLANG]

583
00:33:47,563 --> 00:33:49,063
Tighten your grip!

584
00:34:12,896 --> 00:34:16,354
[CHARIOT WHEEL CREAKS]

585
00:34:16,396 --> 00:34:28,688
♪ ♪

586
00:34:28,688 --> 00:34:30,146
WOHOO!

587
00:34:30,729 --> 00:34:32,938
WOHOO!
[IN UNISON]

588
00:34:35,021 --> 00:34:37,313
Is the procession on?
Who's pushing it?

589
00:34:37,354 --> 00:34:39,146
It's us, Sir!

590
00:34:46,146 --> 00:34:47,688
[CHENNA SCREAMS]

591
00:34:47,688 --> 00:34:49,438
How the hell did
you get up here?

592
00:34:49,438 --> 00:34:50,688
You got me here, right?

593
00:35:09,604 --> 00:35:14,438
[FRANTIC SHOUTING AND SCREAMING]

594
00:35:21,479 --> 00:35:24,438
[OVERLAPPING COMMOTION]

595
00:35:24,438 --> 00:35:25,521
Scoundrels!

596
00:35:25,563 --> 00:35:27,813
Don't you see?!
It's me! Chenna!

597
00:35:28,521 --> 00:35:30,229
Scumbags! Let me come to you!

598
00:35:40,521 --> 00:35:41,729
[BERME SCREAMS]

599
00:35:42,354 --> 00:35:43,813
Who was that woman?!

600
00:35:44,938 --> 00:35:46,521
Hey! He's here! Assemble!

601
00:35:54,021 --> 00:35:55,313
HEY!

602
00:36:15,896 --> 00:36:17,563
Behind my back, eh?!
Come at me!

603
00:36:29,688 --> 00:36:30,854
Dodda!

604
00:36:36,396 --> 00:36:38,604
Wait! No! Where are you going?!

605
00:36:38,604 --> 00:36:40,063
Whoa!

606
00:36:40,829 --> 00:36:41,954
Hold it tight!

607
00:36:42,252 --> 00:36:43,336
I'll find a way out!

608
00:37:02,354 --> 00:37:03,688
Why are you
staring like chimps?!

609
00:37:03,729 --> 00:37:04,771
Jump to the side!

610
00:37:11,854 --> 00:37:13,604
What's that noise?!

611
00:37:14,938 --> 00:37:16,021
Dharu!

612
00:37:16,021 --> 00:37:18,021
There's a turn ahead! Good Lord!

613
00:37:18,063 --> 00:37:19,188
Stop the chariot!

614
00:37:21,813 --> 00:37:24,646
Oh no! There's a valley at the end!

615
00:37:29,271 --> 00:37:31,979
Lord Eshwara! Please save me!

616
00:37:32,021 --> 00:37:34,854
I vow to break coconuts during
the Brahma-Kalasha! Good Lord!

617
00:37:38,271 --> 00:37:40,854
[MEN SCREAM IN UNISON]

618
00:37:50,729 --> 00:37:52,438
Give us some time!
We'll come by ourselves.

619
00:37:52,438 --> 00:37:53,521
I just shat my pants!

620
00:37:53,938 --> 00:37:56,188
After all, you needed
soldiers to rescue you.

621
00:37:58,563 --> 00:37:59,729
Bring them!

622
00:38:00,271 --> 00:38:02,104
- Princess!
- Hey, Chenna!

623
00:38:03,063 --> 00:38:04,396
What are you doing with them?

624
00:38:06,271 --> 00:38:08,896
I put my life on the line to arrest them!

625
00:38:09,021 --> 00:38:10,563
JAI BANGRA!

626
00:38:10,729 --> 00:38:12,188
JAI BANGRA!
[DRUNK DHAARU]

627
00:38:19,271 --> 00:38:20,354
What is this?

628
00:38:20,438 --> 00:38:22,438
- Country liquor.
- Specially made by us.

629
00:38:28,979 --> 00:38:30,396
WHOA!

630
00:38:31,438 --> 00:38:33,354
This packs a solid punch!

631
00:38:36,146 --> 00:38:37,229
Yeah.

632
00:38:37,521 --> 00:38:38,688
Keep this inside.

633
00:38:38,729 --> 00:38:39,938
We shall leave now.

634
00:38:41,729 --> 00:38:43,396
We've given it.
We shall take your leave.

635
00:38:49,146 --> 00:38:50,354
Chieftain!

636
00:38:54,479 --> 00:38:57,229
King, these men were
stealing goods in the market.

637
00:38:57,271 --> 00:38:59,646
When questioned, they went
wild and damaged our businesses.

638
00:39:00,854 --> 00:39:02,479
What is it.. your name?

639
00:39:02,729 --> 00:39:03,854
Berme.

640
00:39:03,938 --> 00:39:05,229
Where did you come from?

641
00:39:05,271 --> 00:39:06,604
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

642
00:39:06,604 --> 00:39:07,729
Kantara.

643
00:39:09,938 --> 00:39:12,188
[STEEL CLASHES AS WEAPONS ARE DRAWN]

644
00:39:13,729 --> 00:39:15,354
I hope the Brahma-rakshasa isn't here.

645
00:39:17,688 --> 00:39:19,021
[CHAIN CLASHES]

646
00:39:23,146 --> 00:39:25,271
[WHIP CRACKS]

647
00:39:33,521 --> 00:39:34,938
I can't do this anymore.

648
00:39:35,313 --> 00:39:36,688
They're built like buffaloes.

649
00:39:37,813 --> 00:39:39,563
Kantara?!

650
00:39:39,604 --> 00:39:40,729
[WHIP CRACKS]

651
00:39:40,729 --> 00:39:42,021
Brahma-rakshasa.

652
00:39:42,604 --> 00:39:43,729
[WHIP CRACKS]

653
00:39:43,979 --> 00:39:48,021
You trapped my grandfather while
he was out hunting and killed him!

654
00:39:48,021 --> 00:39:49,188
Treacherous brutes!

655
00:39:49,604 --> 00:39:51,354
They don't bruise easily!
Whip them harder!

656
00:39:51,475 --> 00:39:55,479
Bhogendra, their dummy
forest has nothing in it!

657
00:39:55,521 --> 00:39:56,729
It's all a sham!

658
00:39:56,729 --> 00:39:59,479
If you're truly your father's son,
you'd have stood your ground.

659
00:39:59,521 --> 00:40:00,938
You'd have seen
that sham turn real.

660
00:40:01,563 --> 00:40:03,938
The kid ran and I could
see his bum was on fire.

661
00:40:03,979 --> 00:40:06,479
[MEN LAUGH IN UNISON]

662
00:40:06,479 --> 00:40:08,521
[DIBBA] Don't laugh guys!
They'll beat us harder!

663
00:40:11,771 --> 00:40:13,396
What are you
staring at them for?!

664
00:40:13,438 --> 00:40:14,604
Go on! Whip them!

665
00:40:15,021 --> 00:40:17,563
[OVERLAPPING GRUNTS]

666
00:40:21,229 --> 00:40:23,146
Proud of beating tied-up
men, you scumbag?

667
00:40:23,188 --> 00:40:24,396
Unchain me and come at me.

668
00:40:27,271 --> 00:40:28,271
WHAT?!

669
00:40:28,313 --> 00:40:29,896
S-C-U-M-B-A-G.

670
00:40:31,021 --> 00:40:33,313
Please don't laugh!
They'll whip us harder!

671
00:40:37,271 --> 00:40:38,354
Kulashekhara!

672
00:40:40,604 --> 00:40:41,688
Step back!

673
00:40:42,813 --> 00:40:43,979
Now!

674
00:40:48,604 --> 00:40:50,646
[BHOGENDRA] We were only watching.

675
00:41:05,813 --> 00:41:08,021
Who brought you to Bangra?

676
00:41:09,063 --> 00:41:10,854
Is your Bangra
floating up in the sky?

677
00:41:10,896 --> 00:41:12,521
Four steps and
anybody can find it.

678
00:41:12,521 --> 00:41:13,688
We came by ourselves.

679
00:41:13,729 --> 00:41:14,979
God! Save me!

680
00:41:15,979 --> 00:41:17,688
- Hey!
- Oh. Chenna.

681
00:41:18,604 --> 00:41:20,021
Where's your uniform?

682
00:41:20,271 --> 00:41:21,313
I'm sick.

683
00:41:21,771 --> 00:41:23,313
I came to ask the
commander for leave.

684
00:41:23,479 --> 00:41:24,813
- Did he grant it?
- Yes.

685
00:41:25,229 --> 00:41:26,979
Permanent leave. See you.

686
00:41:28,979 --> 00:41:30,438
What about the secret service?

687
00:41:30,438 --> 00:41:31,688
There are other men doing it.

688
00:41:31,729 --> 00:41:33,063
My wife's easier to deal with.

689
00:41:33,271 --> 00:41:34,771
Why did you come here?

690
00:41:35,396 --> 00:41:36,896
You came to check on us.

691
00:41:37,354 --> 00:41:38,771
Can't we do the same?

692
00:41:40,854 --> 00:41:42,813
[BROODING MUSIC BUILDS]

693
00:41:42,896 --> 00:41:44,354
Did you go to Kantara?

694
00:41:44,729 --> 00:41:46,104
We didn't go inside.

695
00:41:46,604 --> 00:41:48,438
We looked around the borders.

696
00:41:48,688 --> 00:41:52,438
[MEN OF KANTARA LAUGH IN UNISON]

697
00:41:52,479 --> 00:41:54,229
You knew you wouldn’t return home.

698
00:41:54,271 --> 00:41:56,146
Yet you stepped onto this land?

699
00:41:56,646 --> 00:41:59,563
[BROODING MUSIC BUILDS]

700
00:42:00,271 --> 00:42:02,646
Back in the day, we
let you return home.

701
00:42:03,271 --> 00:42:06,479
Today we barge into your kingdom,
beat your men, and stand before you.

702
00:42:09,313 --> 00:42:11,438
You really think we can't go back?

703
00:42:11,479 --> 00:42:14,146
[BROODING MUSIC BUILDS]

704
00:42:28,896 --> 00:42:29,896
Come here.

705
00:42:30,438 --> 00:42:31,563
NOW!

706
00:42:34,063 --> 00:42:37,846
Did you drop some salt or poured it?!

707
00:42:39,063 --> 00:42:40,063
Hey.

708
00:42:40,146 --> 00:42:41,354
Nothing to worry!

709
00:42:41,354 --> 00:42:42,979
Just asking him
if there's enough salt.

710
00:42:45,438 --> 00:42:47,813
They've strolled in like it’s
a trip, hands swinging free.

711
00:42:47,813 --> 00:42:49,104
Those hands must be cut...

712
00:42:49,146 --> 00:42:50,563
He doesn't like an ordinary guy.

713
00:42:50,938 --> 00:42:54,104
The way he carries himself, he
seems like he's the leader of Kantara.

714
00:42:54,146 --> 00:42:56,313
Exactly! Exactly why I'm telling you!

715
00:42:56,479 --> 00:42:58,021
We'll not get this
opportunity again.

716
00:42:58,021 --> 00:42:59,521
He’s in our hands.
Let’s finish him.

717
00:42:59,563 --> 00:43:00,604
Yep.

718
00:43:00,646 --> 00:43:03,396
If you were in good company,
you'd understand a king's duty.

719
00:43:04,104 --> 00:43:05,896
Keep cuddling your duty.

720
00:43:06,063 --> 00:43:07,313
What will it be now?

721
00:43:14,021 --> 00:43:16,521
Let’s not make enemies
of Kantara’s people.

722
00:43:18,729 --> 00:43:21,688
Sigh! It's all in your
hands, isn't it, my king?

723
00:43:22,063 --> 00:43:23,771
Do I have your permission
to wash my hands?

724
00:43:24,021 --> 00:43:25,188
Hey!

725
00:43:27,188 --> 00:43:28,229
Argh!

726
00:43:28,746 --> 00:43:30,121
Hot water?! You wretched fellow!

727
00:43:30,146 --> 00:43:33,229
[SERVANT SCREAMS IN PAIN]

728
00:43:38,938 --> 00:43:39,979
Well...

729
00:43:55,021 --> 00:43:56,438
MY CHILD!

730
00:43:57,771 --> 00:43:59,479
[IN TULU] Sleeping, my child?

731
00:44:00,229 --> 00:44:01,604
Wake up!

732
00:44:04,813 --> 00:44:07,146
It's been a couple of
days since the children left.

733
00:44:07,521 --> 00:44:10,229
Please make sure they stay safe.

734
00:44:10,688 --> 00:44:11,771
Swami!

735
00:44:14,188 --> 00:44:15,521
We've got prisoners.

736
00:44:15,521 --> 00:44:17,188
Sell them to the
Arabs for a good price.

737
00:44:17,188 --> 00:44:18,521
I can't just sell anyone man!

738
00:44:18,563 --> 00:44:20,896
Want me to sell you?
I'll dress you like a monkey and sell!

739
00:44:20,938 --> 00:44:23,479
You're giving me toothpicks
and are insisting that I sell them!

740
00:44:23,479 --> 00:44:25,063
It's really difficult, Bhogendra.

741
00:44:25,063 --> 00:44:27,313
Hey! Don't you dare call
me by my name, Booba.

742
00:44:27,438 --> 00:44:29,438
- I'm now a minister.
- I see.

743
00:44:29,521 --> 00:44:34,021
When I was guarding the King, your father
didn’t even know where babies came from.

744
00:44:34,063 --> 00:44:36,479
Today, you're calling me
out by my name - "Booba!"

745
00:44:36,479 --> 00:44:38,521
Hey! Where the heck is Booba?!
[IN PORTUGUESE]

746
00:44:38,563 --> 00:44:40,146
- Hey! Excuse me!
- What do you want?

747
00:44:40,146 --> 00:44:42,063
There's no space
to dock my boat.

748
00:44:42,104 --> 00:44:44,229
What the heck is
this port even for?

749
00:44:44,229 --> 00:44:46,229
- What did he say?
- He's a Portuguese trader.

750
00:44:46,229 --> 00:44:47,729
He claims there's
no space to dock.

751
00:44:47,729 --> 00:44:49,563
He's asking if the port
is only for decoration?

752
00:44:53,896 --> 00:44:54,979
[SHARP SLAP]

753
00:44:55,604 --> 00:44:57,479
You see there’s no
place to dock, right?

754
00:44:57,479 --> 00:44:59,563
Next time, try
swimming to the port.

755
00:44:59,729 --> 00:45:00,854
Get lost!

756
00:45:01,104 --> 00:45:02,229
Son of a tramp!

757
00:45:02,229 --> 00:45:03,479
Hey! What the hell did he say?

758
00:45:03,521 --> 00:45:05,354
- He cursed your mother...
- Whoa! Calm down!

759
00:45:05,396 --> 00:45:07,479
He just called you
an 'aggressive man'!

760
00:45:08,938 --> 00:45:09,938
HEY!

761
00:45:10,563 --> 00:45:11,854
Remember!

762
00:45:11,979 --> 00:45:13,521
'The son of a tramp!'

763
00:45:14,271 --> 00:45:15,813
Idiot! I'll take you to task someday!

764
00:45:16,021 --> 00:45:17,396
- Honourable Minster!
- Yeah?

765
00:45:17,396 --> 00:45:19,354
You shouldn't be laying
your hands on foreigners.

766
00:45:19,688 --> 00:45:21,188
It'll ruin our trade.

767
00:45:21,229 --> 00:45:23,604
Some folks only feel the
love when it comes with a slap.

768
00:45:23,646 --> 00:45:24,979
The men I've got now are strong.

769
00:45:25,021 --> 00:45:26,229
Shut your bum and sell them!

770
00:45:26,229 --> 00:45:27,313
- Oy!
- Is food here?

771
00:45:27,313 --> 00:45:29,729
Check out the strong
men you got last time!

772
00:45:30,896 --> 00:45:32,646
Nothing! Checking
if you were alive.

773
00:45:32,688 --> 00:45:33,688
Go back to sleep.

774
00:45:33,729 --> 00:45:35,438
I thought food was here.

775
00:45:35,563 --> 00:45:37,646
The men I’ve brought
today are no ordinary men.

776
00:45:37,688 --> 00:45:40,438
They razed King
Street to the ground.

777
00:45:40,854 --> 00:45:42,313
Our King Street?

778
00:45:42,604 --> 00:45:44,271
How dare they!

779
00:45:44,313 --> 00:45:47,521
These dacoits deserve to
be handled by my son, Peppe!

780
00:45:47,729 --> 00:45:53,938
[INTENSE ORCHESTRAL SCORE]

781
00:45:55,646 --> 00:45:56,813
Hand me the whip!

782
00:45:57,188 --> 00:45:58,396
Swami is here.

783
00:46:08,729 --> 00:46:10,479
[METAL KEY CLANGS]

784
00:46:10,479 --> 00:46:12,146
[HEAVY METAL DOOR OPENS]

785
00:46:16,604 --> 00:46:19,146
No matter how loud it gets
in here, you don’t hear a thing.

786
00:46:20,021 --> 00:46:21,146
- Got it?
- Yes.

787
00:46:23,938 --> 00:46:25,063
Latch the gates shut.

788
00:46:25,438 --> 00:46:26,438
Pardon me?

789
00:46:27,521 --> 00:46:29,104
Latch the damn gates!

790
00:46:29,104 --> 00:46:30,188
Sure.

791
00:46:32,354 --> 00:46:34,021
This isn't for the faint-hearted

792
00:46:34,146 --> 00:46:35,354
Wait outside.

793
00:46:35,563 --> 00:46:37,438
Okay. Hey! Get out!

794
00:46:37,438 --> 00:46:39,104
No one comes back
until we order you to.

795
00:46:46,021 --> 00:46:47,104
[WHIP CRACKS]

796
00:46:53,146 --> 00:46:54,813
How dare you rob
under my watch?!

797
00:46:54,813 --> 00:46:55,896
Lowlifes!

798
00:46:55,896 --> 00:46:57,021
Where are you from?

799
00:46:57,021 --> 00:46:58,188
Where did you come from?!

800
00:47:01,438 --> 00:47:02,521
Kantara.

801
00:47:02,563 --> 00:47:04,313
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

802
00:47:04,354 --> 00:47:05,354
What?!

803
00:47:07,021 --> 00:47:08,063
Kantara.

804
00:47:24,563 --> 00:47:26,688
Hurry up, dumbo!

805
00:47:26,688 --> 00:47:29,604
I asked them to latch it and
morons have locked the damn gates!

806
00:47:29,604 --> 00:47:30,771
What are you saying?!

807
00:47:31,771 --> 00:47:35,479
Oy! If anyone's around,
please open the gates.

808
00:47:35,896 --> 00:47:38,188
- Anybody out there?
- Is Swami calling us?

809
00:47:38,229 --> 00:47:41,521
Swami told us to turn
deaf ears to all their cries.

810
00:47:41,521 --> 00:47:42,729
It's me, Peppe calling!

811
00:47:42,771 --> 00:47:44,521
Don't be afraid.
We are harmless!

812
00:47:44,521 --> 00:47:46,146
HEY!

813
00:47:47,104 --> 00:47:49,521
Morons! Hurry up
and open the gates!

814
00:47:49,521 --> 00:47:50,938
My life's at stake!

815
00:47:50,979 --> 00:47:53,354
I beg you! I'm suffocating in here!

816
00:47:53,354 --> 00:47:55,063
Oy! Come here!

817
00:47:56,771 --> 00:47:58,313
Ay! Sit down!

818
00:48:01,271 --> 00:48:02,896
Thank god they're here!

819
00:48:02,938 --> 00:48:05,479
- Remember you're bloody guards!
- What happened to Sir?

820
00:48:05,479 --> 00:48:07,771
Keeps poking his head in
matters that don't concern him.

821
00:48:07,813 --> 00:48:09,521
You call this guarding?

822
00:48:09,563 --> 00:48:11,229
Where the heck did you go?!

823
00:48:11,229 --> 00:48:13,688
We went to take a dump in the open.
– Together, like a squad?

824
00:48:13,729 --> 00:48:15,271
Sir has ordered us to stick together!

825
00:48:15,271 --> 00:48:16,979
Stick with me dammit!
Not on your own!

826
00:48:16,979 --> 00:48:19,229
Where did you find
these numb-nuts?!

827
00:48:19,229 --> 00:48:20,521
You'll have it from me!

828
00:48:20,563 --> 00:48:22,521
Move, scumbag! Give me my sword!

829
00:48:22,563 --> 00:48:23,604
Where are you off to?!

830
00:48:23,604 --> 00:48:25,146
Mongrels! Get my head out!

831
00:48:27,561 --> 00:48:29,313
- Close it!
- Now lock the gates!

832
00:48:30,688 --> 00:48:32,104
All the shouting was of no use!

833
00:48:37,586 --> 00:48:38,829
Don't come closer!

834
00:48:38,854 --> 00:48:40,563
I'm a builder sure,
but I'm not into wood!

835
00:48:41,229 --> 00:48:42,313
We won’t hurt you.

836
00:48:42,521 --> 00:48:43,896
We’re humans, just like you.

837
00:48:50,271 --> 00:48:51,646
Why did they imprison you?

838
00:48:53,563 --> 00:48:57,479
My family has done
a lot for Bangra.

839
00:48:57,646 --> 00:49:00,646
King Vijayendra asked
us to build a palace.

840
00:49:00,646 --> 00:49:01,646
I built it.

841
00:49:01,729 --> 00:49:04,188
His son asked us to build a prison.

842
00:49:04,396 --> 00:49:05,688
We built that too...

843
00:49:05,854 --> 00:49:08,479
Not even in my worst
dreams did I imagine

844
00:49:08,521 --> 00:49:10,938
they’d use my own
prison to jail me.

845
00:49:11,063 --> 00:49:12,479
S.. S.. Sankappa.

846
00:49:12,521 --> 00:49:13,563
Whose Appa?

847
00:49:13,563 --> 00:49:14,604
Yep.

848
00:49:15,104 --> 00:49:16,896
I am that wretched man.

849
00:49:16,896 --> 00:49:18,438
Sankappa! God!

850
00:49:18,479 --> 00:49:20,729
Never did I imagine that I
would get to touch your feet.

851
00:49:20,771 --> 00:49:22,813
Bangra's people said
these very words at first.

852
00:49:22,854 --> 00:49:24,521
Do tell us. Why did they jail you?

853
00:49:24,563 --> 00:49:26,563
The King asked for a ship.

854
00:49:26,563 --> 00:49:28,313
- Did you build one?
- I did.

855
00:49:28,604 --> 00:49:33,396
To test it, they made my trusted aide, the
Commander take the ship out to the river.

856
00:49:33,563 --> 00:49:39,604
Right before our eyes, the ship sank,
taking the Commander down with it.

857
00:49:39,646 --> 00:49:40,646
But why?

858
00:49:40,688 --> 00:49:45,771
We’d made a tiny hole in the
bottom, just to drain rainwater.

859
00:49:46,021 --> 00:49:50,354
But I never imagined water would
flood in through that same little hole.

860
00:49:50,354 --> 00:49:51,479
Dammit!

861
00:49:51,771 --> 00:49:54,479
That’s why you
don’t drink on the job.

862
00:49:54,604 --> 00:49:57,313
Drink all you want after work.

863
00:49:57,354 --> 00:49:59,313
That mishap actually
helped the Commander.

864
00:49:59,354 --> 00:50:01,271
But that thankless fool
should remember it, no?

865
00:50:01,313 --> 00:50:02,313
Hey!

866
00:50:02,854 --> 00:50:04,771
What's that? A town by the river?

867
00:50:04,979 --> 00:50:07,354
That's the market by the sea.

868
00:50:07,604 --> 00:50:08,688
A port.

869
00:50:08,729 --> 00:50:12,104
[DRAMATIC SCORE]

870
00:50:13,479 --> 00:50:15,229
[PEPPE WALKS IN]

871
00:50:15,729 --> 00:50:16,771
Looks like they're here.

872
00:50:16,771 --> 00:50:17,979
[DOOR BREAKS OPEN]

873
00:50:17,979 --> 00:50:19,021
[MEN GASP]

874
00:50:20,771 --> 00:50:22,479
I haven't seen daylight in years!

875
00:50:22,521 --> 00:50:24,896
Good Lord! Scoundrel's here!

876
00:50:34,354 --> 00:50:36,188
You can come!
I'm holding the gate tightly!

877
00:50:41,829 --> 00:50:42,829
Oy.

878
00:50:44,021 --> 00:50:46,188
Quit staring and hold
the gate, scoundrels!

879
00:50:48,729 --> 00:50:50,604
Don't worry. We're holding it from inside.

880
00:50:55,949 --> 00:50:57,824
Heard you wanted to talk.

881
00:50:57,896 --> 00:50:58,938
What's the matter?

882
00:51:00,104 --> 00:51:01,188
Gosh!

883
00:51:02,396 --> 00:51:03,688
We’ve got plenty more of that.

884
00:51:04,854 --> 00:51:06,479
Let us out and we’ll fetch it for you.

885
00:51:07,271 --> 00:51:08,646
We’ll give you half

886
00:51:09,188 --> 00:51:10,688
And trade the rest.

887
00:51:11,688 --> 00:51:13,396
He got hold of trading so soon?!

888
00:51:14,104 --> 00:51:15,354
Not happening!

889
00:51:15,396 --> 00:51:18,021
You've been sold for 1000
Varaahas to the Arabs.

890
00:51:23,271 --> 00:51:24,396
What are you smoking?

891
00:51:25,104 --> 00:51:26,938
Tobacco.
From beyond the seas.

892
00:51:27,021 --> 00:51:28,021
It stinks.

893
00:51:29,479 --> 00:51:30,938
I'll give you something.
Wanna smoke?

894
00:51:31,063 --> 00:51:32,146
What is it?

895
00:51:32,479 --> 00:51:34,104
You get some wild herbs in our forests.

896
00:51:34,979 --> 00:51:36,104
Wild herb?!

897
00:51:36,104 --> 00:51:37,229
Smoke it!

898
00:51:37,396 --> 00:51:38,563
You'll be flying!

899
00:51:40,188 --> 00:51:46,854
[TRIPPY MUSIC ENSUES]

900
00:51:46,854 --> 00:51:49,188
[METAL CHAINS RATTLE]

901
00:51:52,146 --> 00:51:53,771
What quality herbs, man!

902
00:51:54,646 --> 00:51:57,021
Feels like the prison gates are wide open.

903
00:51:57,396 --> 00:51:59,479
Sir, the cell gates are open.

904
00:51:59,938 --> 00:52:00,938
Exactly.

905
00:52:02,646 --> 00:52:04,646
- Sir Peppe!
- Enough. Give me some.

906
00:52:05,188 --> 00:52:06,354
About us trading?

907
00:52:06,521 --> 00:52:07,521
Tell me this.

908
00:52:07,854 --> 00:52:11,396
You think saying "trade" a
few times makes you a trader?

909
00:52:11,688 --> 00:52:13,688
Do you even know what it means?

910
00:52:13,854 --> 00:52:14,938
Forget that.

911
00:52:14,938 --> 00:52:18,271
Ever seen what
a port looks like?

912
00:52:19,771 --> 00:52:20,771
Can we?

913
00:52:27,188 --> 00:52:29,479
Nothing tops this.

914
00:52:30,146 --> 00:52:33,854
I need to kiss the hands of
the saint who blessed us with it.

915
00:52:36,229 --> 00:52:37,271
What are you doing?

916
00:52:37,771 --> 00:52:38,771
Disgusting!

917
00:52:38,813 --> 00:52:42,479
My old man never goes back on his word.

918
00:52:42,646 --> 00:52:43,979
Saw the port, right?

919
00:52:44,021 --> 00:52:45,479
It's dark. Now leave.

920
00:52:46,354 --> 00:52:47,896
[BOOBA SNORING LOUDLY]

921
00:52:48,705 --> 00:52:50,539
He dozed off?

922
00:52:50,854 --> 00:52:52,313
[METAL LATCH CLANGS]

923
00:52:53,188 --> 00:52:54,313
Done?

924
00:52:54,646 --> 00:52:55,688
Yep.

925
00:52:55,729 --> 00:52:57,979
You can't open it, can you?

926
00:53:00,688 --> 00:53:02,271
No matter how hard I try, I can't.

927
00:53:02,604 --> 00:53:03,688
Sleep.

928
00:53:04,063 --> 00:53:05,396
We'll talk in the morning.

929
00:53:06,188 --> 00:53:07,438
Sankappa, let's go.

930
00:53:09,563 --> 00:53:10,729
We'll see you.

931
00:53:10,938 --> 00:53:13,104
Don’t want them thinking
we left without a word.

932
00:53:14,063 --> 00:53:15,813
Let Booba know once he's up!

933
00:53:16,979 --> 00:53:18,646
What quality herbs, man!

934
00:53:22,604 --> 00:53:24,229
You don't look like
someone from Kantara.

935
00:53:24,563 --> 00:53:25,771
Oh no. I'm an Arab.

936
00:53:25,813 --> 00:53:27,563
My father came to trade
and I was born here.

937
00:53:27,604 --> 00:53:29,479
Looks like man
traded for a lot more!

938
00:53:29,813 --> 00:53:32,396
Having seen the outside
world, Berme realized

939
00:53:32,396 --> 00:53:34,688
his people needed
a leader to prosper.

940
00:53:35,479 --> 00:53:36,646
Let’s start farming!

941
00:53:36,813 --> 00:53:38,146
What does that mean, son?

942
00:53:38,188 --> 00:53:41,646
Nothing tough. Let us grow
whatever we wish to eat.

943
00:53:41,979 --> 00:53:43,729
♪ Prosperity.. Flourishing.. Produce ♪

944
00:53:43,729 --> 00:53:45,354
♪ Prosperity.. Everywhere ♪

945
00:53:45,396 --> 00:53:48,604
♪ Beneath the blue moonlight,
we witness our first harvest ♪

946
00:53:48,938 --> 00:53:55,521
♪ Golden rays have ripened
into fruition in Kantara ♪

947
00:54:00,396 --> 00:54:02,229
♪ Fresh gooseberries rest in our palms ♪

948
00:54:02,229 --> 00:54:03,271
Go on.

949
00:54:03,729 --> 00:54:05,771
♪ Learning to wield the
machines comes easily now ♪

950
00:54:05,813 --> 00:54:07,313
Thank God! It turned.

951
00:54:07,354 --> 00:54:10,729
♪ We’ve built stairs to the
floor above, a ladder to the sky ♪

952
00:54:10,979 --> 00:54:14,729
♪ And now we dream in colours ♪

953
00:54:14,938 --> 00:54:16,979
♪ Our eyes glimmer with a newfound light ♪

954
00:54:16,979 --> 00:54:18,396
♪ Aaha! Ohoo! ♪

955
00:54:18,396 --> 00:54:19,813
Phew! My job's done.

956
00:54:19,854 --> 00:54:21,896
♪ Aaha! Yeheee! ♪

957
00:54:21,938 --> 00:54:23,979
♪ Our gait has now got style ♪

958
00:54:23,979 --> 00:54:25,396
♪ Aaha! Ohoo! ♪

959
00:54:25,438 --> 00:54:27,438
♪ The forest shimmers with a gleam ♪

960
00:54:27,479 --> 00:54:28,854
♪ Aaha! Yeheee! ♪

961
00:54:28,854 --> 00:54:30,604
♪ Prosperity.. Flourishing.. Produce ♪

962
00:54:30,646 --> 00:54:32,271
♪ Prosperity.. Everywhere ♪

963
00:54:32,271 --> 00:54:34,563
♪ Beneath the blue moonlight,
we witness our first harvest ♪

964
00:54:34,604 --> 00:54:35,979
Swami Panjurli has blessed us.

965
00:54:36,021 --> 00:54:37,938
- Berme, it's a boy.
- Great.

966
00:54:37,938 --> 00:54:39,729
It's great to see
your zeal in this age.

967
00:54:39,771 --> 00:54:40,813
Come on!

968
00:54:41,521 --> 00:54:43,646
By the time he grows up,
Kantara will have everything.

969
00:54:44,604 --> 00:54:52,813
♪ ♪

970
00:54:52,813 --> 00:54:54,896
♪ Ay! Plough and see ♪

971
00:54:56,063 --> 00:54:58,479
- What is all this for, my son?
- For trading, Abba.

972
00:54:58,521 --> 00:54:59,729
What does trading mean?

973
00:54:59,854 --> 00:55:01,938
We barter this for what we need.

974
00:55:03,688 --> 00:55:05,854
♪ Bask in this harvest song ♪

975
00:55:06,771 --> 00:55:08,729
♪ Ay! Plough and see ♪

976
00:55:08,771 --> 00:55:10,479
♪ Ay! Strive and earn ♪

977
00:55:10,646 --> 00:55:13,813
♪ Savor the forest and hills,
bask in this harvest song ♪

978
00:55:14,146 --> 00:55:17,604
♪ To give and receive,
the finest way to live ♪

979
00:55:17,646 --> 00:55:20,771
♪ Trust your strength
and live your lives ♪

980
00:55:20,938 --> 00:55:22,979
♪ Our eyes glimmer with a newfound light ♪

981
00:55:23,021 --> 00:55:24,354
♪ Aaha! Ohoo! ♪

982
00:55:24,354 --> 00:55:25,771
♪ This soil now yields fresh produce ♪

983
00:55:25,813 --> 00:55:29,021
We no longer keep the third
share at the forest’s edge.

984
00:55:30,229 --> 00:55:31,771
How long will you
live in fear of being

985
00:55:31,813 --> 00:55:33,604
killed by them if you
step out of the forest?

986
00:55:33,933 --> 00:55:36,600
When they live so arrogantly,
relying only on their puny soldiers.

987
00:55:37,604 --> 00:55:40,479
Imagine if we, with the Daivas'
strength, set foot on their land.

988
00:55:40,479 --> 00:55:41,979
♪ Prosperity.. Everywhere ♪

989
00:55:41,979 --> 00:55:48,729
♪ Golden rays have ripened
into fruition in Kantara ♪

990
00:55:54,938 --> 00:55:57,313
Old man! Don't drink too much!

991
00:55:57,521 --> 00:55:59,229
You'll lose your bladder!

992
00:55:59,396 --> 00:56:02,021
Ever since the
Kantara folks ran off

993
00:56:02,396 --> 00:56:04,313
My life has been lost.

994
00:56:04,604 --> 00:56:08,146
What will I do with this gallbladder, son?

995
00:56:08,188 --> 00:56:10,688
We've got to do something to find them.

996
00:56:10,729 --> 00:56:11,854
Done already.

997
00:56:11,979 --> 00:56:14,188
If we nab them, I’ve made a vow.

998
00:56:14,229 --> 00:56:19,563
To send my son on a
14-year exile in that forest.

999
00:56:19,688 --> 00:56:21,354
That should work, right?

1000
00:56:22,146 --> 00:56:23,563
- Booba!
- Huh?

1001
00:56:23,646 --> 00:56:25,563
How dare you call
your father by name?

1002
00:56:25,604 --> 00:56:26,771
Scoundrel!

1003
00:56:28,063 --> 00:56:30,021
That wasn't me.

1004
00:56:30,021 --> 00:56:32,063
- Boobanna! [IN UNISON]
- Who?!

1005
00:56:33,521 --> 00:56:34,979
- Berme!
- Namaskara!

1006
00:56:35,021 --> 00:56:37,771
No! I'm not going to
the forest, Old man!

1007
00:56:37,813 --> 00:56:39,479
Jail these crooks!

1008
00:56:39,521 --> 00:56:41,521
- Now!
- What for, Boobanna?

1009
00:56:41,563 --> 00:56:45,896
We spent 1000 Varaahas of our own
to buy you, just to sell you to the Arabs.

1010
00:56:45,896 --> 00:56:48,646
That is our entire lifetime's
earnings, damn you!

1011
00:56:49,938 --> 00:56:51,146
Poor you.

1012
00:56:52,813 --> 00:56:55,479
Boobanna, we’ll trade right
here and repay your debt.

1013
00:56:56,188 --> 00:56:57,438
Really?

1014
00:56:59,729 --> 00:57:00,854
You've to repay.

1015
00:57:02,021 --> 00:57:04,313
- I swear on you.
- Okay. Go.

1016
00:57:04,354 --> 00:57:05,479
Good people.

1017
00:57:05,521 --> 00:57:06,813
- Old man!
- Yeah?

1018
00:57:06,813 --> 00:57:08,854
Did you just
permit them to trade?

1019
